<TITLE> Work to revamp BNP will resume after meeting: Hannan Shah </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 13 (bdnews24.com)  BNP chief Khaleda Zia's adviser ASM Hannan Shah Thursday said he would resume activities to revamp the party after discussions with the policymaking standing committee. "The leader is in jail. We discussed how the party could be activated through discussions with the standing committee members with whom we hope to talk soon," he said to reporters after a meeting with the joint secretaries general and organising secretary of the party in Mohakhali. Party joint secretaries general Selima Rahman, Goyeshwar Chandra Roy, Prof MA Mannan and organising secretary Mohammad Shahjahan were present. The meeting discussed prevailing political situation, unity process, party programme for March 26 as well as other organisational matters. Hannan demanded release of Khaleda by Dec 26, Independence Day. He expressed the hope to unite the two streams in the party and said, "I have started the unity process at the directive of the leader. I am hopeful about this." Asked whether he had consulted the secretary general on the March 26 programme, he said, "The secretary general is in the US. I don't have his telephone number. There is no need to consult the secretary general to fix the programmes." bdnews2
